description: Beef Bhuna is a popular Bangladeshi dish made with tender chunks of beef cooked in a spicy tomato-based sauce. Khondoker Amir Uddin is a master chef in Bangladesh known for his skill in preparing traditional dishes like Beef Bhuna.

Chingri Malai Curry is a classic Bangladeshi dish that features jumbo prawns cooked in a rich and creamy coconut milk sauce. Nirob is a renowned Bangladeshi chef who is known for his expert use of spices and herbs in his cooking.

Chicken Korma is a flavorful Bangladeshi dish that is made with succulent chicken pieces cooked in a creamy yogurt and spice-based sauce. Rahima Begum is a talented Bangladeshi chef who has perfected the art of cooking classic Bangladeshi dishes like Chicken Korma.

Biriyani is a classic Bangladeshi dish made with spiced rice and either chicken, beef, or fish. Tommy Miah is a renowned Bangladeshi chef who has popularized this dish in the UK, where he has been awarded an MBE for his contribution to the culinary industry.

Fuchka is a popular street food in Bangladesh, consisting of small fried balls filled with spiced potato or chickpeas, served with a tamarind or mint chutney. Tahmina Islam is a talented Bangladeshi chef who has taken this humble street food and elevated it to a gourmet level with her own unique twist.

Kacchi Biriyani is a traditional Bangladeshi dish made with spiced rice and marinated goat meat or beef that is slow-cooked in a sealed pot for hours. Shawkat Osman is a highly skilled Bangladeshi chef who has perfected the art of cooking this complex dish.

Pitha is a type of sweet or savory cake that is popular in Bangladesh, especially during the winter months. Jhuma Akhtar is a skilled Bangladeshi chef who specializes in making a variety of pitha using traditional methods and ingredients.

Dhokla is a popular snack in Bangladesh made from fermented batter made from rice and split chickpeas. Shanta Rahman is a Bangladeshi chef who specializes in making this dish using fresh ingredients and spices.

Shorshe Ilish is a popular Bangladeshi dish made with Hilsa fish cooked in a mustard sauce. Mamun Chowdhury is a master chef in Bangladesh known for his expertise in cooking seafood dishes like Shorshe Ilish.

Bhapa Pitha is a popular sweet dish in Bangladesh made with rice flour and coconut, and steamed in banana leaves. Sharmin Rahman is a skilled Bangladeshi chef who has perfected the art of making this traditional dish, and adds her own unique twist with the addition of jaggery and cardamom.

Chitol Maacher Muitha is a popular Bangladeshi dish made with fish meatballs cooked in a spicy tomato and onion sauce. Farhana Haque is a talented Bangladeshi chef who has put her own unique twist on this traditional dish, adding a touch of sweetness with jaggery and raisins.

Dhaka Biryani is a famous Bangladeshi dish made with fragrant basmati rice, tender meat, and a blend of spices. Nazrul Islam is a renowned Bangladeshi chef who has perfected the art of making this delicious dish, using his secret blend of spices and cooking techniques passed down from generations.

Shami Kebab is a popular Bangladeshi appetizer made with minced meat, lentils, and spices. Sadia Rahman is a skilled Bangladeshi chef who has taken this classic recipe and added her own unique twist with the addition of pomegranate seeds, giving the kebabs a tangy and fruity flavor.

Jhal Muri is a spicy and crunchy snack made with puffed rice, vegetables, and a variety of spices. It's a popular street food in Bangladesh. Shahin Alam is a skilled chef who has elevated this humble snack with his own unique blend of spices and herbs.

Patla Khichuri is a popular comfort food in Bangladesh made with rice, lentils, and a variety of spices. Aminul Islam is a skilled Bangladeshi chef who has perfected this traditional dish with his own unique blend of spices and cooking techniques.
